##
## Kiro Linux — Chaotic-AUR mirrorlist (curated, robust default)
##
## Ships on the live ISO and is copied to the installed system. Kept short on
## purpose: the two official Chaotic-AUR CDN mirrors, which geo-route each user
## to their nearest up-to-date datacenter. This overrides the long country list
## that the chaotic-mirrorlist package would otherwise drop in, for the same
## reason the Arch mirrorlist is trimmed — fast, complete, no dead-mirror tail.
##

## Geo mirror — automatic routing to the geographically closest up-to-date mirror
Server = https://geo-mirror.chaotic.cx/$repo/$arch

## CDN mirror — global content-delivery network (fallback)
Server = https://cdn-mirror.chaotic.cx/$repo/$arch
